      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Commercial CFD solver with documented V&V history and version control; solver release notes reviewed.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent 2022R2 is a commercially validated solver with documented quality assurance processes. Release notes and known-issue logs were reviewed. Version control applied to all case files and boundary condition scripts. Required level 2 is met."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/ncv-001",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver benchmarked against published analytical solutions for laminar pipe flow and rotating disk problems.",
      "rationale": "The solver was verified against Hagen-Poiseuille analytical solutions and Couette flow benchmarks documented in the ANSYS verification manual. Results agreed within 0.3% for all test cases. Required level 2 is met."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/disc-error-001",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) below 5% for hemolysis index QoI across at least three systematically refined meshes; Richardson extrapolation applied.",
      "rationale": "A mesh refinement study was conducted using three mesh densities (4.2 M, 8.7 M, and 16.1 M cells). The observed GCI for the relative hemolysis index ranged from 6.8% to 9.4% across the five operating points, which exceeds the 5% threshold specified for this factor. The team notes that hemolysis predictions in centrifugal pumps are inherently sensitive to near-wall resolution, and the coarser meshes capture global flow features adequately. Engineering judgment supports proceeding, as the hemolysis index trends are directionally consistent across all mesh densities and the RH acceptance criterion is met with margin. Formal Richardson extrapolation was applied only to the two finest meshes; the three-mesh GCI criterion was not fully satisfied."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/test-conditions-001",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental boundary conditions (flow rate, rotational speed, fluid properties) documented and matched to CFD inputs within 2%.",
      "rationale": "Experimental test conditions from the FDA benchmark dataset were reproduced in the CFD model. Flow rates and rotational speeds matched to within 1.1%. Blood analog fluid properties (glycerol-water mixture) were applied consistently. Required level 2 is met."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/output-comparison-001",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "CFD-predicted hemolysis index within 20% of experimental measurements across all five operating points.",
      "rationale": "Predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) values were compared against published FDA experimental measurements. Errors ranged from 4.2% to 17.8% across the five operating points, all within the 20% acceptance criterion. Required level 2 is met."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/relevance-qoi-001",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
