      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoI (relative hemolysis index RH) is directly linked to the COU decision criterion and clinical endpoint.",
      "rationale": "The relative hemolysis index RH is the primary QoI and directly maps to the regulatory acceptance criterion (RH < 1 relative to predicate device). This QoI is clinically meaningful and aligns with FDA guidance on hemolysis assessment. Required level 2 is met."
    },
    {
